$Id$

This is still highly experimental.  To compile the Perl5 bindings for
PLplot, you will need swig and the Perl modules XML::Parser and XML::DOM.
The API chapter of the Docbook documentation is parsed for generating the
function prototypes.

The build process has not yet been integrated into the PLplot package
configuration scheme.  For now, this is the cookbook:

    $ cd bindings/perl5
    $ make -f pkg_perl5.in ln-tmp
    $ cd ../../tmp

You will have to change the $libs variable at the top of api2bind.pl,
reflecting the configuration results in your system.  This variable will be
AC_SUBST'ituted in the future.

    $ make -f pkg_perl5.in (which executes api2bind.pl)

Then run the x01 demo:

    $ ./x01.pl
